ston, Nottinghamshire, England":"英国英格兰諾廷加姆爾洛勒斯頓","England":"英国英格兰","lifeSummary":"当Amfelicia Rolleston于1158年之前出生在英国英格兰諾廷加姆爾洛勒斯頓时，她的父亲Alan FitzRoald de Richmond28岁，母亲Olivia de Croft17岁。她和Joelin de Neville clerk in the Exchequer至少有1个儿子。她去世于1219年之后在英国越可爾皮可爾，埋葬在英国越可爾皮可爾。"},"hr":{"Bef 1158–after 1219":"prije 1158.–nakon 1219.","1158–1219":"1158–1219","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1140–1207":"1140–1207.","1187–1246":"1187.–1246","1130–1201":"1130–1201.","1140–1226":"1140–1226","1187":"1187.","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","Bef 1158":"prije 1158.","1140":"1140","1215":"1215","1226":"1226","1246":"1246","1158":"1158","1201":"1201.","after 1219":"nakon 1219.","1219":"1219","1207":"1207.","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Pickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Pickhill, Yorkshire, England","Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England":"Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","England":"Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"Bef 1158–after 1219":"před 1158–po 1219","1158–1219":"1158–1219","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1140–1207":"1140–1207","1187–1246":"1187–1246","1130–1201":"1130–1201","1140–1226":"1140–1226","1187":"1187","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","Bef 1158":"před 1158","1140":"1140","1215":"1215","1226":"1226","1246":"1246","1158":"1158","1201":"1201","after 1219":"po 1219","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Anglie","Pickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Pickhill, Yorkshire, Anglie","Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England":"Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","England":"Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"Bef 1158–after 1219":"før 1158–efter 1219","1158–1219":"1158–1219","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1140–1207":"1140–1207","1187–1246":"1187–1246","1130–1201":"1130–1201","1140–1226":"1140–1226","1187":"1187","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","Bef 1158":"før 1158","1140":"1140","1215":"1215","1226":"1226","1246":"1246","1158":"1158","1201":"1201","after 1219":"efter 1219","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Yorkshire, England":"Jórvík, England","Pickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Pickhill, Jórvík, England","Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England":"Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"Bef 1158–after 1219":"vóór 1158–na 1219","1158–1219":"1158–1219","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1140–1207":"1140–1207","1187–1246":"1187–1246","1130–1201":"1130–1201","1140–1226":"1140–1226","1187":"1187","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","Bef 1158":"vóór 1158","1140":"1140","1215":"1215","1226":"1226","1246":"1246","1158":"1158","1201":"1201","after 1219":"na 1219","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Pickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Pickhill, Yorkshire, England","Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England":"Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Bef 1158–after 1219":"before 1158–after 1219","1158–1219":"1158–1219","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1140–1207":"1140–1207","1187–1246":"1187–1246","1130–1201":"1130–1201","1140–1226":"1140–1226","1187":"1187","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","Bef 1158":"before 1158","1140":"1140","1215":"1215","1226":"1226","1246":"1246","1158":"1158","1201":"1201","after 1219":"after 1219","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Pickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Pickhill, Yorkshire, England","Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England":"Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Rolleston","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["1  English: locative name, in the Midlands from Rolleston (Leics, Notts, Staffs) and perhaps Rowston (Lincs); in ER Yorks from Rolston (or Rowlston) in Mappleton (ER Yorks); and in SW England from Rollestone in Upton Pyne, or Rolstone Barton in Morchard Bishop (both in Devon), or Rollestone (Wilts), and perhaps Rowlestone (Herefs). It is possible that some of the following bearers belong with (2), particularly the Yorks examples.","2  English: relationship name variant of   Rollinson  , reduced to  <i>Rolleson</i> and altered by the addition of an intrusive  <i>-t-</i>, as though it were a locative name in  <i>-ston</i>. Compare Thomas Rolleson’, 1377 in   Poll Tax   (Kingston upon Hull, ER Yorks), and Christopher Rollston, 1723, Henry Rowlstone, 1763 in   IGI   (Kingston upon Hull, ER Yorks)."],"variants":[{"name":"Rollason","meanings":["English:  see  Rollinson  ."]},{"name":"Roleston","meanings":["English:  see  Rolleston  ."]},{"name":"Roulson","meanings":["1  English: chiefly a variant of   Rolleston   with the common reduction of  <i>-ston</i> to  <i>-son</i>.","2  English: relationship name occasionally perhaps from the Anglo-Norman French personal name   Rolfe   +  <i>-son</i>, but this appears to have been a rare surname in the medieval period."]},{"name":"Rollinson","meanings":["English: variant of   Rollison  ."]},{"name":"Roulston","meanings":["English (Leicestershire and Nottinghamshire): variant of   Rolston  ."]},{"name":"Rollston","meanings":["English:  see  Rolleston  ."]},{"name":"Rowlstone","meanings":["English:  see  Rolleston  ."]},{"name":"Rolstone","meanings":["English:  see  Rolleston  ."]},{"name":"Roulstone","meanings":["English:  see  Rolleston  ."]},{"name":"Rolston","meanings":["English (Leicestershire):","habitational name either from Rolleston (Leicestershire, Nottinghamshire, Staffordshire) and perhaps Rowston (Lincolnshire), Rolston (or Rowlston) in Mappleton (East Yorkshire), or from Rollestone in Upton Pyne, or Rolstone Barton in Morchard Bishop (both in Devon), or Rollestone (Wiltshire), and perhaps Rowlestone (Herefordshire) or Rolstone in Banwell (Somerset). The placenames have various etymological origins, though most are named with the Middle English personal name <i>Rolf</i> or the Old Norse personal name <i>Hrólfr</i> + Middle English <i>toun</i> ‘town, settlement’, Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. See   Rolfe  .","variant of   Rollison  , shortened to <i>Rolleson</i> and altered by the addition of an intrusive <i>-t-</i>, as though it were a habitational name in <i>-ston</i>."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":57,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Amfelicia Rolleston was born before 1158, in Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Alan FitzRoald de Richmond, was 28 and her mother, Olivia de Croft, was 17. She had at least 1 son with Joelin de Neville clerk in the Exchequer. She died after 1219, in Pickhill, Yorkshire, England, and was buried in Pickhill, Yorkshire, England."},"et":{"Bef 1158–after 1219":"enne 1158–pärast 1219","1158–1219":"1158–1219","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1140–1207":"1140–1207","1187–1246":"1187–1246","1130–1201":"1130–1201","1140–1226":"1140–1226","1187":"1187","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1130":"1130","Bef 1158":"enne 1158","1140":"1140","1215":"1215","1226":"1226","1246":"1246","1158":"1158","1201":"1201","after 1219":"pärast 1219","1219":"1219","1207":"1207","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Pickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Pickhill, Yorkshire, England","Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, England":"Rolleston, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Bef 1158–after 1219":"ennen vuotta 1158–1219 jälkeen","1158–1219":"1158–1219","1165–1252":"1165–1252","1140–1207":"1140–